<br>
I liked halfling due to sneak / hide, which in my eyes let me be a little more independant in getting around and not always needing to bug someone for invis. The exp bonus was a nice lil kick too.<br>
<br>
But at one time our guild had an ogre war that was in worse equip than all of us, and he appeared to do a better job tanking.. So I started up an ogre war and got him 53 and did like the character, cept for the size.. I couldnt stand the ogre size and not being able to move around well in places.. Then I kinda made the mistake of making the ogre war on my guildleaders account and then that guild fell apart, so I quit playing the ogre and then lost access to the account shortly after. Another guildie DID restart from a halfling war to an ogre war and he still plays now as the ogre. If I did it over again, I may pick ogre, but then again, I do like being different and being a halfling as well as the small size and exp bonus.. And with the new AA skills, the no stuns thing probably won't matter too much, nor does the sta. <p>&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=213175&quot;&gt;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=213175&lt;/a&gt;<br>
