<br>
Holding aggro and focusing attention to a mob makes a warrior a warrior.  This can be done with any class.  An ogre hold an upper edge because of the slam factor and the hit points.  If a warrior can add aggro to some mobs (granted this is a tad passive since many of the high end arena's are unstunnable), this is obviously beneficial to holding aggro.  Even more so is the fact that you can live through it.  If you have an additional 1khp, that is obviously a big advantage.  <br>
<br>
After a while though I see that all classes and all races can get items enough to make up for the loss of initial stats, which allows us to turn back to what so many others focused on here...<br>
<br>
What do you enjoy playing the most?  What roleplay seems the most fun?  Is there anything you can do as one race that you cannot do as another that would put you bar none against the others?  Are you having fun as that class?<br>
<br>
I have seen a Human Warrior hold aggro better than a Barbarian warrior.  I have seen a Half Elf outlive an Ogre time and again on the same raid.  I have seen paladin's out-MA the Warriors of the same class and level.  Honestly, there is a lot of things that factor into this, but in the end there really is only one question....<br>
<br>
Are you having fun as &quot;x&quot;?<br>
<br>
For me, I love the way my Dark Elf Warrior is played and what he adds to any given situation.  He is my pride and joy in so many ways and I would not give him up for the world.  I have fun playing a DE warrior, and as this is a game, that is what it is all about....  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just had to add my two cents in here, even though so many others have said what I did.  It may not be new, but it is from me. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users.rcn.com/cooley2/ashsig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.supernovah.com/images/bronzestar_swing_md_wht_5113.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.supernovah.com/images/BrandonBronze.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
